15.  The DTRs of the Agency personnel assigned in the City and other offices be prepared based on their logbooks and signed by the Department Heads or any appropriate authority of the City Government as a control measure to ensure that services rendered are based on actual days of work;

16.  The Agency provide, on a regular basis, a pro-forma survey form to each Department/Office Head for the latter to rate the performance of the Agency Personnel and the City, as a whole, for the betterment of such service;

17. That claims for 13th month pay on a monthly basis be discontinued and be paid only in the middle and/or end of the year on or before December 24, duly supported with certified payroll of personnel entitled to receive thereto;

18. The five days SILP be granted to qualified Agency personnel, in case they have not availed of the five-day vacation leave with pay during CY 2020. Onwards, in lieu of the SILP, the Agency personnel should be allowed to avail the five-day vacation leave with pay during the year;

19. The City GSO and the Accountant ensure that only actual services rendered are paid and that contributions are duly remitted in the correct amount by the Agency to the SSS and PHIC;

20. The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) ensure that compliance with social legislation and other applicable laws are part of the eligibility requirements in the procurement of janitorial and security services. Post-qualification must be done on the previous transactions made detailing the contractor’s compliance with labor standards and social legislation and those payments to its personnel are adequately given; and

21. The revision of the Contract Agreement to properly indicate as to who will pay the expenses for training of Agency security personnel.

