We recommended the following:

The Accounting Office as in-charge of the keeping of the books of accounts, use the proper accounts under the IPSAS and faithfully adhere to its implementation to ensure a fair presentation of accounts in the City’s FS; submit a correct and accurate financial report considering the recognition of Receivable Accounts, Cost of Sales, and the corresponding accounts relative to the sale and lease agreements of the C3. In addition, submit basis and/or justification on the material changes in the balances of the accounts; 

That management establishes a specific policy and operational guidelines to implement the modified accrual basis of accounting, not only for income but also for expenditures, as well, after evaluating the effects thereof to the respective accounts, in order to improve the quality, coverage, timeliness, and relevance of the City’s financial data and ensures compliance with the IPSAS.

We recommended that management:

a.  Faithfully comply with the relevant provisions of the laws, rules and regulations governing the administration of LDRRMF to be assured that government resources are administered and used properly, regularly and legally according to the purposes for which the fund was created;

b.  Ensure that all processes and documentations prescribed under other relevant laws and rules are duly complied with for disbursement to be valid and proper, necessary and effective in consonance with the purpose sought to be attained;

c. Submit the LDRRMFIP for CY 2016 and years thereafter as per Section 5.1.2 of COA Circular No. 2012-002 and the correct Utilization Report (Section 5.1.5) to ensure that LDRRM Funds are properly recorded and accounted for.

