observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:

a. The LCE prioritize the conduct of physical inventory of all the City’s properties by the Inventory Committee and cause the submission of an updated and complete RPCPPE duly reconciled with accounting and property records to properly establish the existence, ownership and valuation of the PPEs and ensure its fair presentation in the FS;

b. The Accounting Unit reclassify to the Public Infrastructure account all concreting and asphalting of city and barangay roads, and construction of drainage systems recorded and depreciated under the Land Improvements account of ₱14,632,324.07 and adjust accordingly the corresponding depreciation and repair and maintenance, to the Prior Year’s Adjustment account;

c. For the Accounting Office and CGSO to observe proper recording of transactions relating to supplies and property of the City Government, maintain their respective records which contains complete data/information, which in turn will support the PPE accounts as appearing in the FS;

d.  The CGSO to identify the insurable physical assets, submit the required reports and insure the City’s properties with the GSIS pursuant to COA Circular No. 92-390 to protect the government against property losses.

e.  The City Government and the DepEd City Schools Division Office establish an internal control policy or agreement for the effective property management and accountability of all PPE charged against SEF to establish the actual existence and condition of the property accountabilities purportedly issued to DepEd officers (and for all the other offices of the City Government, for this matter) and as such ensure that:

accountability over issued property items is established at any point in time;

the AREs are prepared and updated regularly or whenever there is a change of accountability over the item; and

the existence and condition of the PPE items are reasonably determined every year.

f.  Copies of the JEVs taking up the reclassifications/adjustments should be separately submitted to COA for verification.

