We recommended that the LFC ensure that appropriate measures are in place to control not only the appropriations, allotments, and cash availability but proper implementation of PPAs. The Treasurer should also implement control measures in the proper disposition of the cash accounts particularly cash pertaining to trust and/ or special funds received by the City Government to ensure that:

a.  Cash is deposited intact in the proper books of accounts, i.e., trust receipts should be directly received, deposited and recorded in the TF books of accounts;

b.  Amounts due for remittances, like the BIR, GSIS, etc., should be remitted within the reglementary period to avoid penalties and/or other sanctions that may be imposed by the BIR and other regulatory bodies;

c.  Cash disbursements are made only for valid transactions pertaining to the particular fund to avoid suspension/s and/or disallowance/s in audit;

d.   PPAs are implemented as planned, prioritized and budgeted in the intended year; and

Adjust and/or correct the obligations in relation to the actual income realized as intended by Section 147 (c) of GAAM, Volume I.

We recommended that:

a.  The City Budget Office prepare and submit the List of Budget Utilizations Not Yet Due and Demandable (Maintenance and Other Operating Expenses and Capital Outlay) as of December 31 of each year (Section 3.5, COA Accounting Circular Letter No. 2007-002 dated 1/19/2007), which provides that “obligations which are not yet recorded as liabilities but are valid commitments based on approved contracts/ purchase orders which are not yet implemented and/or goods are not yet delivered;” 

Include in the annual budget accurate amount for the debt services of the City for the budget year with reference to loan amortization schedules provided by the financial institutions;

b.  The City Treasurer’s Office prepare and submit the List of Accounts Payable, which represents the Disbursement Voucher (DV) and/or Payroll duly processed, approved and ready for payment, i.e. obligations due and demandable;

c.  Management instill internal control on the budget, payment of and recording of their financial transactions and as such:

1.)  The LFC and the Sangguniang Panlungsod (SP), in coming up with a supplemental budget, should be cautious enough to consider the necessary constraints by adhering to RA 7160. When resorting to the reversion of payable accounts, adherence to the policies and procedures and proper authorization be followed;

2.) The City Accounting Office, particularly, the Pre-Audit Division, shall faithfully comply with one of the fundamental principles governing the financial transactions under Section 4(6) of PD 1445 and ensure that transactions are completely documented; and

3.)  The City Accountant to safekeep unpaid DVs and other necessary documents to ascertain the validity, propriety and legality of the various liabilities account in the FS; and to facilitate verification thereof.

We recommended that the Local School Board (LSB):

a. Appropriate funds for PPAs as mandated by law and as prioritized under Section 100 of RA 7160;

b. Programs be within what is allowed.   Exclude activities/ transactions which fall under the exclusions per LOI 1462 in implementation of programs;

c.  Align activities within the mandated priorities to assure compliance as to its appropriation,  authority and payment; and

d. Submit the Report of SEF Utilization duly certified by the City Accountant and the LCE to facilitate monitoring thereof.

We recommended that management:

a.  Faithfully comply with the relevant provisions of the laws, rules and regulations governing the administration of LDRRMF to be assured that government resources are administered and used properly, regularly and legally according to the purposes for which the fund was created;

b.  Ensure that all processes and documentations prescribed under other relevant laws and rules are duly complied with for disbursement to be valid and proper, necessary and effective in consonance with the purpose sought to be attained;

c. Submit the LDRRMFIP for CY 2016 and years thereafter as per Section 5.1.2 of COA Circular No. 2012-002 and the correct Utilization Report (Section 5.1.5) to ensure that LDRRM Funds are properly recorded and accounted for.

We recommended that management should draw a policy/ guidelines, with proper sanctions, on the payment of communication expenses to the City Government’s Officials, Department Heads and other qualified personnel but considering the following factors provided under pertinent laws, rules and regulations:

1.)  Persons authorized to claim;

2.)  Amount to be paid should be the amount actually incurred but not to exceed the reasonable ceiling to be set by management;

3.) Expenses incurred are official in nature and necessary in the performance of duties and functions and the mandate of the office and the City Government as a whole; and

4). Disbursements are advantageous to the government.

We recommended that the City develop a procedural flow as follows:

Upon receipt of an ObR, the Budget Officer:

1.) Pre-evaluate the completeness of supporting documents;

2.)  Prepare, process and sign the ObR;

3.)  Record obligation incurred in the (electronic) control file and in the respective Registry of Appropriation (RAO) (separate registries should be maintained); and

4.) Forward to Accounting Office, the duly signed ObR.

We recommended that the City Accountant ensure that the LDDRMF accounting and reporting guidelines per COA Circular No. 2012-002 be followed such as:

a. An SL by year and source for unexpended Quick Response Fund (QRF) and MOOE-DRRMF in the Trust Liability-DRRM in the TF books be maintained;

b. An LDRRMIP in accordance in the prescribed format be prepared which shall include the current year’s appropriation and incorporating the unutilized balances of the previous years;

c. The CDRRMO submit timely reports on the Sources and Utilization of DRRMF prepared by the City Accountant on or before the 15th day at the end of each month;

d. Create and maintain a separate depository account for DRRM transfers; and

e.  Incorporate in the Notes to FS, a tabular presentation of the amount available, utilized and balance of the LDRRMF in prescribed format.

